		</div>

		I&#8217;ve been told to pay more attention to the Trusted Computing Group, which is pushing hardware-based digital IDs and security. Microsoft (with Palladium), and Intel (with the forthcoming LaGrande) are major players in the group, along with HP, IBM, and AMD.
		
